version: 1.2.0

## Changelog

### 1.2.0 (2026-04-03)
- PreToolUse hook: ammo-msg-check.sh — gates champion agents mid-turn when undelivered teammate messages exist (forces turn end so messages get delivered)
- Gate 5.1b v2: unified accuracy gate (opt_accuracy >= baseline_accuracy)
- Removed 3-mode token-level comparator (exact_greedy, topk_relaxed, first_divergence_topk)
- Increased max_tokens from 256 to 1024
- Increased default n from 30 to 200
- Added metadata mismatch detection (num_questions + max_tokens)
- Added baseline_accuracy=0 infrastructure error check
- Tiered profiling strategy: probe-driven Tier 0 (nsys node) / Tier 1 (torch.profiler Chrome traces) / Tier 2 (nsys graph enrichment)
- New reference: torch-profiler-guide.md (Chrome trace parsing, multi-rank analysis, kernel chains, BW estimation, occupancy caveats)
- Sweep script: --torch-profile and --nsys-mode flags with per-bucket profiler lifecycle
- nsys_probe.py: compute_tier_recommendation() with SM100 detection, probe failure handling
- verify_phase1_baseline.py: accepts Chrome traces alongside nsys-rep files
- Evidence rules: Chrome trace accepted as Tier 3 evidence (debate-rules.md, validation-defaults.md)
- 9 new conformance test scenarios (R9-R12, O21) + 5 probe failure tests

### 1.1.0 (2026-04-02)
- feat: redesign Gate 5.1b as E2E correctness via GSM8K greedy decode (replaces token-level comparison with deterministic generation matching against golden references)
- refactor: simplify Stage 5 — validator is now a champion-spawned sub-agent (not an orchestrator-spawned team member), handling Gates 5.1a + 5.2; champion owns Gates 5.1b + 5.3a + 5.3b via single sweep script invocation
- feat: add accuracy-risk scoring for quantization-inclusive optimizations — lossy/lossless classification system with dtype boundary rule, separate speedup accounting (2x lossless / 4x lossy deflation), mandatory topk_relaxed + 100 GSM8K questions for lossy tracks, undisclosed precision reduction penalties, Phase 0 eligibility gate for classification
- Updated agents: ammo-champion, ammo-impl-champion, ammo-impl-validator, ammo-transcript-monitor
- Updated orchestration: debate-protocol, parallel-tracks, integration-logic
- Updated references: debate-scoring-rubric, validation-defaults
- Updated skill: SKILL.md (state.json schema, sweep script usage)
- New test scenarios: test-impl-champion.md (IC1–IC10 conformance tests)

### 1.0.0 (2026-03-31)
- Initial versioned release of AMMO session config
- Agents: ammo-champion, ammo-impl-champion, ammo-impl-validator, ammo-transcript-monitor, ammo-delegate, ammo-researcher
- 7-stage campaign pipeline with adversarial debate, parallel worktree tracks, GPU pool management
- References: debate-scoring-rubric, validation-defaults, impl-track-rules, gpu-pool, cudagraph-safety, gpu-configs, code-templates, kernel-benchmark-template
